eb.pdf|title= Radiation Protection and the Management of Radioactive Waste in the Oil and Gas Industry |date=2003 |publisher= [[International Atomic Energy Agency]] |accessdate=20 May 2012  |format = PDF | pages = 39\u201340}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"IPR bromide\">{{cite news |url=http://www.loe.org/blog/blogs.html/?seriesID=1&blogID=32 |title=Disposal of Fracking Wastewater Polluting PA Rivers|author1=Bruce Gellerman |author2=Ann Murray |work=PRI's Environmental News Magazine|date=10 August 2012 |publisher=Public Radio International|accessdate=14 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Kim\">Kim, Won-Young  [http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/7c4754d6-0a81-11e3-9cec-00144feabdc0.pdf 'Induced seismicity associated with fluid injection into a deep well in Youngstown, Ohio'], Journal of Geophysical Research-Solid Earth</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"live\">{{cite press release |url= http://live.psu.edu/story/63286 |title= Analysis of Marcellus flowback finds high levels of ancient brines |publisher= [[Pennsylvania State University]] |date= 17 December 2012 |accessdate= 31 January 2013 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20130114065954/http://live.psu.edu/story/63286 |archive-date= 14 January 2013 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"LoganJeffrey\">{{cite report |title=Natural Gas and the Transformation of the U.S. Energy Sector: Electricity |first=Jeffrey |last=Logan |publisher= Joint Institute for Strategic Energy Analysis | url=http://www.nrel.gov/docs/fy13osti/55538.pdf | year = 2012 | format = PDF |accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Lutz 2013\">{{Cite journal |last=Lutz |first=Brian |last2=Lewis |first2=Aurana |last3=Doyle |first3=Martin |title=Generation, transport, and disposal of wastewater associated with Marcellus Shale gas development |date=8 February 2013 |journal=Environmental Health Perspectives |pages=647\u20131197 |volume=49 |issue=2 |doi=10.1002/wrcr.20096|bibcode=2013WRR....49..647L |url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/8a6abe8a24958efa91cc6