ing Regions | first =Mindy |last=Lubber |date=28 May 2013 |work= [[Forbes]]|accessdate=20 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"guardian10022013\" >{{cite news |url =https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2013/oct/02/dangerous-radioactivity-fracking-waste-pennsylvania|title=Dangerous levels of radioactivity found at fracking waste site in Pennsylvania. Co-author of study says UK must impose better environmental regulation than US if it pursues shale gas extraction | first =Felicity |last=Carus |date=2 October 2013 |newspaper= The Guardian | accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"HassBenjamin\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-14/fracking-hazards-obscured-in-failure-to-disclose-wells.html |title=Fracking Hazards Obscured in Failure to Disclose Wells |first=Benjamin |last=Hass |date=14 August 2012 |newspaper=Bloomberg News |accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"HeatOnGas\">{{cite journal|last=Brown |first=Valerie J. |title=Industry Issues: Putting the Heat on Gas |date=February 2007 |journal=Environmental Health Perspectives |volume=115|issue=2 |pages=A76 |pmc=1817691|pmid=17384744 |doi=10.1289/ehp.115-a76}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hfstudy\">{{cite web |url=http://www.epa.gov/hfstudy/ |title=EPA's Study of Hydraulic Fracturing and Its Potential Impact on Drinking Water Resources |publisher=EPA |accessdate=24 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"house1\">{{cite web|url=http://democrats.energycommerce.house.gov/sites/default/files/documents/Hydraulic-Fracturing-Chemicals-2011-4-18.pdf |publisher=Committee on Energy and Commerce U.S. House of Representatives |title=Chemicals Used in Hydraulic Fracturing |date=April 18, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004213846/http://democrats.energycommerce.house.gov/sites/default/files/documents/Hydraulic-Fracturing-Chemicals-2011-4-18.pdf |archivedate=2013-10-04 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"IAEA 2003\">{{cite report |url=http://www-pub.iaea.org/MTCD/publications/PDF/Pub1171_web.pdf|title= Radiation Protection and the Management of Radioactive Waste in the Oil and Gas Industry |date=2003 |publisher= [[International Atomic Energy Agency]] |accessdate=20 May 2012  |format = PDF | pages = 39\u201340}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"IPR bromide\">{{cite news |url=http://www.loe.org/blog/blogs.html/?seriesID=1&blogID=32 |title=Disposal of Fracking Wastewater Polluting PA Rivers|author1=Bruce Gellerman |author2=Ann Murray |work=PRI's Environmental News Magazine|date=10 August 2012 |publisher=Public Radio International|accessdate=14 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Kim\">Kim, Won-Young  [http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/7c4754d6-0a81-11e3-9cec-00144feabdc0.pdf 'Induced seismicity associated with fluid injection into a deep well in Youngstown, Ohio'], Journal of Geophysical Research-Solid Earth</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"live\">{{cite press release |url= http://live.psu.edu/story/63286 |title= Analysis of Marcellus flowback finds high levels of ancient brines |publisher= [[Pennsylvania State University]] |date= 17 December 2012 |accessdate= 31 January 2013 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20130114065954/http://live.psu.edu/story/63286 |archive-date= 14 January 2013 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"LoganJeffrey\">{{cite report |title=Natural Gas and the Transformation of the U.S. Energy Sector: Electricity |first=Jeffrey |last=Logan |publisher= Joint Institute for Strategic Energy Analysis | url=http://www.nrel.gov/docs/fy13osti/55538.pdf | year = 2012 | format = PDF |accessdate=27 March 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Lutz 2013\">{{Cite journal |last=Lutz |first=Brian |last2=Lewis |first2=Aurana |last3=Doyle |first3=Martin |title=Generation, transport, and disposal of wastewater associated with Marcellus Shale gas development |date=8 February 2013 |journal=Environmental Health Perspectives |pages=647\u20131197 |volume=49 |issue=2 |doi=10.1002/wrcr.20096|bibcode=2013WRR....49..647L |url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/8a6abe8a249